---
Verification Capabilities
=========================

Supported test kinds:
  - property

Unsupported test kinds:
  - unit [intentional]: Unit tests have no fuzzer input domain; formal verification requires universally quantified properties.
  - benchmark [intentional]: Benchmarks measure performance, not correctness; they have no boolean property to verify.

Target modes:
  - property
  - validator (requires validator metadata)
  - equivalence (requires validator metadata)

Supported fuzzer output types:
  - Int
  - Bool
  - ByteArray
  - String
  - Data
  - List<T>
  - Tuple(T, ...)
  - Pair(T, T)
  - Finite nullary ADT constructor domains (Data.Constr tag [])

Unsupported fuzzer output types:
  - Blaster translation gaps for some generated Lean predicates (e.g. List.Mem)
  - Test arity > 1 is not supported directly; multi-input properties must be tuple/record encoded.
  - General higher-order/partial-application fuzzer resolver coverage is incomplete; unresolved shapes require extractor improvements.

Existential modes:
  - witness
  - proof

Max test arity: 1

Error catalogue:
